            TripDetails("Hotel","Savera Hotel","Savera Hotel - Chennai's first ever star hotel is an iconic landmark with a fusion of modernity and tradition, cherished by guests for decades now!","4707","#146 Savera Dr Radha Krishnan Salai, Chennai 600004 India","Chennai","13.0460","80.2611",R.drawable.savera,"044 2811 4700",4.2,"http://saverahotel.com"),
            TripDetails("Hotel","GreenPark","For over 25 years, brand GreenPark has stayed true to its fundamental belief – superior service backed by a pragmatic approach to hospitality. With this focus on service quality, we have gained an enviable expertise in blending business with comfort across all our properties. Reason why our guests keep coming back for the GreenPark experience. Explore our properties. We are certain you will agree with our brand of hospitality.From a quick jog before a hearty breakfast to a relaxing foot massage before your journey back home, at GreenPark Chennai, every facility has been thought through to make your stay memorable. Just 12 km from the airport and 15 minutes from the city’s commercial hub, GreenPark Chennai is a hotel few businessmen skip in their itinerary.","6665","# Arcot Road Vadapalani, Chennai 600026 India","Chennai","13.0510","80.2084",R.drawable.greenpark,"044 6651 5151",4.3,"http://www.hotelgreenpark.com/chennai/"),
            TripDetails("Restaurant","Avartana","\n" + "Avartana exemplifies an exclusive blend of traditional and progressive renditions of Southern Indian cuisine, which is rooted to the gravitas of the unique tastes, aromas and flavours of southern Indian spices.\n" + "The Southern Indian Peninsula is unified by the region’s bounty of pepper and spices. Our offerings forge this unity and encompass a range of specially crafted tasting menus for discerning diners, who may choose to enjoy the pleasures of savouring an array of delicacies crafted by our chefs.\n" + "Pronounced ‘avartan’, the word Avartana means rhythm, iteration, mysticism and magic.\n" + "As the restaurant seeks to represent a new interpretation of South Indian cuisine in contemporary renditions, the name Avartana encapsulates the intention of offering different iterations that revolve around this unique cuisine.\n" + "Presenting Southern Indian cuisine- reinvented and redefined","0","# ITC Grand Chola Hotel, Little Mount, Guindy, Chennai, Tamil Nadu 600032","Chennai","13.0105","80.2207",R.drawable.avartana,"044 2220 0000",4.8,"https://www.itchotels.in/hotels/chennai/itcgrandchola/dining/avartana.html"),
            TripDetails("Things to do","Lakkom_Falls","Lakkom_Falls is located between Munnar and Pallivasal. It is a panoramic view but assumes a cascading and roaring beauty during the monsoons. It is one of the most attractive scenes that you can look at during your stay at Munnar. Attukal, 9 km away from Munnar, must be visited for its charming sceneries, glittering waterfalls and rolling hills is a feast for the eyes. The place is also ideal for long trekking and hiking but assumes a cascading and roaring beauty during the monsoons.","0","# Munnar - Udumalpet Rd, Marayoor, Kerala 685620","Munnar","10.1888","77.1115",R.drawable.lakkom_waterfalls,"04865 231 587",4.4,"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lakkom_Falls"),
            TripDetails("Hotel","Parakkat Nature Hotels & Resorts","The resort boasts 50 luxuriously appointed rooms ranging from classic(no tea valley view), superior(few rooms are offering tea valley view), premium(offering tea valley view) and club suites(offering tea valley view) equipped with every modern convenience and amenities. The magnificent reception lounge, the coffee shop with its unique waterfall and 360 degree view of the well kept tea gardens below and the restaurant serving the very best culinary delicacies specially prepared by our international chefs.Nature related activities are available like Jeep safari,Nature walk into the 'Tea Garden',Camp fire etc.","7433","# 2nd Mile, Pallivasal, Munnar 685565 India","Munnar","10.0403","77.0368",R.drawable.parakkat_nature_hotels,"082816 33111",4.4,"http://www.parakkatresorts.com"),
            TripDetails("Restaurant","Al buhari","Indian, Asian, Diner, Arabic\n"+"Vegetarian Friendly, Vegan Options, Halal\n"+"Breakfast, Lunch, Dinner, Brunch","0","# Colony Road, Opp Plathottam Maruthi Service Centre, Ikka Nagar, Munnar, Kerala 685612","Munnar","10.0877","77.0668",R.drawable.al_buhari,"094472 78562",3.5,"https://dyuru.com/munnar/al-buhari-restaurant-munnar/"),
            TripDetails("Hotel","Hotel Great Jubilee","Hotel Great Jubilee is one of the best 3 star business class hotels in Sulthan Bathery, Wayanad, Kerala. It is promoted by V.N.K Group and offers a budget and luxury accommodation with great hospitality. Hotel Great Jubilee encounters all the modern facilities geared up to meet and exceed customer expectations. We provide different types of A/C and Non A/C Rooms that are convenient for a comfortable stay. There are variety of tour packages like weekend, leisure, family and honeymoon packages which will entertain every guest. Efficient services and peaceful atmosphere filled with the flavours of this beautiful land in Wayanad, will offer travellers a lasting memory. Service with smile is what we believe in.","2053","# Main Road Wayanad,Kerala, Sultan Bathery 673592 India","Wayanad","11.6624","76.2544",R.drawable.hotel_great_jubilee,"095260 02244",4.2,"http://www.hotelgreatjubilee.in"),
            TripDetails("Restaurant","Barbeque Nation","Barbeque Nation is one of the most successful casual dining restaurant chains in India. Our restaurants are spacious and well appointed with a lot of wood and open-brick wall surfaces to get you in the mood for a nice and relaxing evening with friends, colleagues or family members. The entire cuisine is a happy blend of American, Mediterranean, Oriental and Indian and is available in both vegetarian and non-vegetarian choices. Our unique 'live-grill' - embedded on your table - allow you and your friends to sit around it and experience the warmth of a barbeque party right at your table. You can grill your own starters in a choice of flavours","0","# No. 39, 1st Floor, Star City Serviced Apartment, Bazullah Rd, Near Grand Sweets, T. Nagar, Chennai, Tamil Nadu 600017","Chennai","13.0478","80.2347",R.drawable.barbeque_nation,"044 6480 6060",4.2,"https://www.barbequenation.com/?utm_source=google_my_business_barbeque_nation&utm_medium=google_my_business&utm_campaign=google_my_business_SEO_Click"),
            TripDetails("Restaurant","Wilton Restaurant","Many would attribute the best Restaurant in town to sheer dedication and hard work. We would say in our case genes had their role too …\n" + "We inherited from our Father Neeliyath Hassan Haji an unrelenting passion to tickle your taste buds. He taught us the art of cooking food and serving love.\n" + "If we were to recall our legacy of running the number one Restaurant in Sulthan Bathery for the last two decades, his instant response would be, “I have done it thrice in three different places my kids.”","0","# S Bathery near Decor, Sultan Bathery 673592 India","Wayanad","11.6587","76.2469",R.drawable.wilton_restaurant,"04936 226 444",4.4,"http://wiltonrestaurant.com"),
            TripDetails("Things to do","Meenmutty Falls","Meenmutty Falls is located 29 km from Kalpetta in Wayanad District in the state of Kerala, India.It is a three-tiered waterfall with a height of 300 metres.Meenmutty is a combination of Malayalam words Meen (fish) and Mutty (blocked). Meenmutty Falls can be reached thorough a 2 km hike though the jungle from the Wayanad-Ooty road.Meenmutty waterfalls are dangerous during rainy seasons due to high inflow and many people have drowned since 1991.","0","# Kalpetta, India","Wayanad","8.7122","77.1452",R.drawable.meenmutty_falls,"9847055110",4.0,"http://www.inwayanad.in/2012/01/how-to-reach-meenmutty-waterfalls-in.html"),
            TripDetails("Things to do","Pagoda Point","Located in the eastern part of the Yercaud Hills, Pagoda point is a beautiful viewpoint where one is treated to a panoramic view of the entire town of Salem as well as the neighbouring village of Kakambadi. The twists and turns of the 21 hairpin bends of Yercaud can be seen from this spot as they envelop themselves around the hills. The mysterious piles of stones arranged in the form of a pyramid resembling a Pagoda give the location its unique name. These stones are believed to be placed here by local tribes.\n" + "\n" + "Between the Pagodas here lies a temple devoted to Lord Rama. One can indulge in the amazing natural beauty of the spot and the scenery of the Eastern Ghats, with the greenery growing within the rugged terrains of the hills, entwined with sights of the craggy cliffs. The sunrise and sunsets at this viewpoint are quite lovely, and late evenings allow visitors to view the magnificent panoramic view of a lit-up Salem. The weather and tranquillity of this spot make the visit worth the trouble.","0","# Pagoda Point Road, Yercaud, Tamil Nadu 636601","Yercaud","11.7664","78.2390",R.drawable.pagoda_point,"",4.1,"https://tamilnadu-favtourism.blogspot.com/2016/05/pagoda-point-pyramid-point-yercaud.html"),
            TripDetails("Hotel","TGI Star Holidays Yercaud","TGI STAR HOLIDAYS is centrally located amidst the tall silver oak trees, mountains and Yercaud Lake nearby and easy access to tourist places. The resort offers 60 well appointed rooms including cottages, multi cuisine restaurant, coffee lounge, large banquet hall for 400 pax, swimming pool, room service, outdoor lawn, shuttle court, table tennis, children play area, basketball court and amphitheatre.\n","5603","# Opp. Union Office, Near Yercaud Lake, Salem Main Road, Yercaud, Tamil Nadu 636602","Yercaud","11.7844","78.2040",R.drawable.tgi_star_holidays,"096552 49206",4.1,"http://www.tgihotels.com/tgi-star-holiday-resort-yercaud/"),
            TripDetails("Restaurant","Altitude Kitchen & Bar (PoolSide)","Romantic Location\n"+"Open to Sky Restaurant\n"+"Local Cuisine\n"+"It simulates two of your sense organs...Eye and tongue for sure Ambience is awesome. Hangs on the edge of a cliff.Very limited seats,so you can feel the silence of the hills.One side has hills,other has pool,garden etc which are highly maintained.","0","# Grand Palace Hotel & Spa | Killiyur Falls Road, Yercaud 636602, India","Yercaud","11.7866","78.2030",R.drawable.altitude_kitchen,"073730 562556",4.3,"http://www.grandpalaceyercaud.com/dining/altitude-kitchen-bar/"),
            TripDetails("Hotel","Sinclairs Retreat","Enveloped by the clouds at 8000 feet and located exactly where the Queen of Nilgiris was discovered, Sinclairs Retreat Ooty is the highest located hotel in South India and unquestionably the best located hotel in Ooty. The hotel has 79 rooms and suites, and two villas with interiors that are modern and charming. The luxurious rooms are equipped with tea/coffee makers and cable TV. The valley view rooms offer stunning views.The resort is equipped with an array of facilities. This includes a Wi-Fi enabled reception area overlooking a three level-landscaped garden, Deluxe, Superior, Premium Suites and Deluxe/Honeymoon suite, conference and meeting facilities; three halls - Regal, The Windsor and The Summit and an open area - The Terrace. Fine dining at Pine n' Petal, a multicuisine restaurant, The Portico, a coffee bar for beverages and snacks, and High Point Bar, a stylish bar and a cool cocktail lounge.The highlight of the property is a vibrant entertainment and recreation zone with indoor badminton, pool table, table tennis, board games, video games, kids play area, library and lounge. Moreover, the hotel comprises of a fitness centre with gym, steam, sauna, and spa.","7080","# 444, Gorishola Road, Thalayathimund, Ooty, Tamil Nadu 643001","Ooty","11.4094","76.7209",R.drawable.sinclairs,"0423 244 4229",3.9,"http://www.sinclairshotels.com/ooty"),
            TripDetails("Things to do","Botanical Gardens","The Government Botanical Garden is a botanical garden in Udhagamandalam, near Coimbatore(Ooty), Tamil Nadu state, India laid out in 1848.The Gardens, divided into several sections, cover an area of around 55 hectares, and lie on the lower slopes of Doddabetta peak.The garden has a terraced layout. It is maintained by the Tamil Nadu Horticulture Department.\n" + "\n" + "It ascends the slopes of the hill at an elevation of 2250–2500 metres above Mean Sea Level.The garden enjoys a temperate climate, with an average rainfall of 140 cm, the most of which is received during south-west monsoon, with frosty nights from November to February.The maximum and minimum temperatures are 28°C and 0°C respectively.","0","# Vannarapettai, Ooty, Tamil Nadu 643002","Ooty","11.4189","76.7114",R.drawable.botanical_garden_ooty,"0423 244 2545",4.3,"https://nilgiris.nic.in/bot_garden.html"),
            TripDetails("Restaurant","Earl's Secret","It's an open secret that when it comes to the finest food in Ooty, there's none other than Earl's Secret, the restaurant at King's Cliff. The favourite of those who prefer fine dining, all in the ambience of lazy historic luxury, Earl's Secret serves continental, mughlai and chinese cuisine. You can sit inside, where the Earls sat, or in the glass house on the lawn.For those not staying at King's Cliff, a reservation might be essential.","0","# Havelock Road, Police Quarters, Pudumund, Ooty, Tamil Nadu 643001","Ooty","11.4199","76.6984",R.drawable.earls_secret,"0423 245 2889",4.2,"http://www.littlearth.in/kingscliff/restaurant.php"),
            TripDetails("Restaurant","Restaurant Ambadi","Designed by British-born, Indian architect Laurie Baker, Hotel Ambadi is swaddled in the breathtaking greenery of the Periyar wildlife Sanctuary. It is just a short walk away, and visitors have immense number of ways to entertain themselves. Sustainable, Eco-Friendly Architecture and Organic Interiors are what stands out in the design by this Padma Shri-awardee. The Naturally Lit and Well-Ventilated rooms and Structures, Inner Courtyards and cool confines of Hotel Ambadi are striking. Founded in 1982, this landmark hotel was named ‘Ambadi‘ by noted filmmaker G. Aravindan and the emblem for Hotel Ambadi was designed by artist Namboothiri, well-known painter and sculptor.","0","# Ambadi Junction,, Periyar, Kerala 685536","Thekkady","9.6027","77.1710",R.drawable.ambadi,"4869-222 193",3.9,"www.hotelambadi.com"),
            TripDetails("Things to do","Chellarkovil Viewpoint","At Chellakovil, you can find a watch tower and there is a telescope placed on the balcony. This balcony is known as 'God's own balcony'. The view from here is great. The most beautiful sight from here is the sunrise and sunset. There is a beautiful waterfall here which is fantastic during the monsoon season. Another specialty of the waterfall is that, the fall originates from Kerala but touches the land at Tamil Nadu irrigating the vegetables and growing plains of Tamil Nadu.","0","# Chellaracovil-Mettu Road, Kerala 685509","Thekkady","9.6699","77.1931",R.drawable.chellarkovil,"",4.2,"https://www.thekkady.com/pages/chellarkovil"),
            TripDetails("Hotel","Amaana Plantation Resort","Amaana Plantation Resort is a stylish, eco friendly resort set amidst pepper and cardamom plantations. Conveniently located, yet far way from the bustle of crowd, it has bountiful treasures of tropical flora and fauna that makes it a pleasant heaven on earth for those who adore nature.","11520","# Amaana Plantation Resort NH 220 Kottayam-Kumily Rd Periyar Kerala 685533, NH 220, Kottayam-Kumily Rd, Periyar, Kerala 685533","Thekkady","9.5930","77.1210",R.drawable.amaana_plantation,"097456 22177",4.5,"http://www.amaanaresorts.com"),
            TripDetails("Things to do","Chinnar Wildlife Sanctuary","Chinnar Wildlife Sanctuary (CWS) is located 18 km north of Marayoor on SH 17 in the Marayoor and Kanthalloor panchayats of Devikulam taluk in the Idukki district of Kerala state in South India. It is one of twelve wildlife sanctuaries among the protected areas of Kerala.","0","# Munnar - Udumalpet Road, Munnar, Kerala 685612","Munnar","10.3069"," 77.2060",R.drawable.chinnar_wildlife_sanctuary,"",4.3,"http://chinnar.org"),
            TripDetails("Restaurant","Hill Spice","An expansive glass-roofed hall, with a long balcony from where you can commune with the tall trees around you, this restaurant has an entrance modelled after the traditional aristocratic architecture of ancient Kerala. Spacious and well laid-out, the service here is prompt and polite. The dishes are made with fresh and organic ingredients. Savoury traditional culinary delights of Kerala and popular South Indian, North Indian and continental dishes may make your choice rather difficult.","0","# P.B. No. 40, Bison Valley Road, Munnar, Kerala 685612","Munnar","10.0488","77.0795",R.drawable.hill_spice,"04865 230 641",3.7,"https://www.ttr.in/restaurant/"),
            TripDetails("Hotel","Swiss County","Misty mountains. Lush green forests. Gurgling streams. Cool Clime. It’s for all these reasons and more that the British referred to Munnar as the ‘Switzerland of India’. Here tucked away in a cozy nook is Swiss County, a small jewel in Munnar’s Crown.","7788","# Chithirapuram Powerhouse Road, Munnar, Kerala 685565","Munnar","10.0308","77.0478",R.drawable.swisscounty,"098466 93700",4.4,"http://www.swisscounty.com"),
            TripDetails("Hotel","Sterling Kodai Valley","Sterling Kodai - Valley is away from the hustle and bustle of the town. Located in a village named Villpatti, the valley is surrounded by pine, oak, and birch trees. Sterling Kodai - Valley is a 122-roomed property that overlooks the valley below. The resort depicts an interesting architecture with a leaf-shaped accommodation block, a lotus-shaped business block, and an array of dome-shaped rooms. Every room has been designed to provide enthralling views. You will also enjoy hiking and trekking in the various nature trails around.","7525","# Attuvampatti, Pallangi Rd, Kodaikanal, Tamil Nadu 624101","Kodaikanal","10.2685","77.4910",R.drawable.sterling_kodai_valley,"04542 244 448",4.2,"https://www.sterlingholidays.com/resorts-hotels/kodaikanal-valley?utm_source=gmb&utm_medium=kodai-valley"),
            TripDetails("Restaurant","Cloud Street","Open for breakfast, snacks, lunch and dinner. Check out the website for the full menu... We love to provide something special for our guests....; To offer friendly hospitality, a genuinely warm welcome. It's important to us that our guests enjoy there time in our place. And not just the food! But with our wood oven and wood grill, we provide some of the best pizzas and grill items you can find for many miles around. Great cakes and coffee too. A comfy place with wifi, music, books and games...","0","1st Floor, Opposite Govt. Tourist Office, P.T. Road, Sunday Market Road, Kodaikanal, Tamil Nadu 624101","Kodaikanal","10.2367","77.4910",R.drawable.cloud_street,"04542 246 425",4.3,"http://www.cloudstreetcafe.com"),
            TripDetails("Things to do","Kodaikanal Lake","Kodaikanal Lake, also known as Kodai Lake is a manmade lake located in the Kodaikanal city in Dindigul district in Tamil Nadu, India. Sir Vere Henry Levinge, the then Collector of Madurai, was instrumental in creating the lake in 1863, amidst the Kodaikanal town which was developed by the British and early missionaries from USA.The lake is said to be Kodaikanal's most popular geographic landmark and tourist attraction.Boating in Kodaikanal Lake.Over the years a boat club, boathouse and boat service (with rowing boats and pedalling boats and a public ferry) for the public and tourists has become fully functional and is of aesthetic significance for tourism. Boat Pageant and Flower Shows are a regular feature in the summer season which attracts tourists.","0","Kodaikanal Road, Kodaikanal, India","Kodaikanal","10.2344","77.4863",R.drawable.kodaikanal_lake,"",4.4,"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kodaikanal_Lake")

        )
    }
}
